      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "First, President Joe Biden passed over potential Supreme Court justice frontrunner Judge Michelle Childs, a union buster propped up by Lindsey Graham, and instead nominated Judge Kentaji Brown Jackson, a former public defender whose recent court history suggests she could be a bit more welcoming to labor efforts. On top of that, despite the risks, dissident voices in Russia are speaking out against Russian President Vladimir Putin’s Ukraine invasion. Finally, a California union just scored a major win for ice cream cake makers. Victory has never tasted so sweet.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "All that and much more in this week’s week’s edition of You Love To See It, exclusively for paying subscribers below.",
