          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "NLRB Tells Starbucks to Kick Rocks",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Starbucks baristas are unionizing. Workers at several stories in upstate New York have petitioned for union elections, following the lead of their colleagues in the Buffalo area. But the company has been trying to slow the elections, asking the National Labor Relations Board not to move forward with voting on the grounds that all stores in the region should vote together in one election. Unfortunately for the company, its attorneys missed a crucial deadline with the NLRB after they failed to turn in all of their paperwork on time. The company missed the cutoff just eight minutes.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As a result of the missed deadline, the NLRB’s regional director ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "ordered",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.huffpost.com/entry/starbucks-tries-to-delay-union-elections-but-misses-legal-deadline-by-8-minutes_n_62104854e4b0f2c343f48992?1agq",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that the company was precluded “from litigating any of the issues raised in its untimely Submission,” despite the company’s attorneys arguing the union, Workers United, “suffered no prejudice” from the delay. The company can appeal the regional director’s order in Washington.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Meanwhile, labor committee chairs from ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "17 states and D.C.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
